sp_instance.title: How to Make Payments to the Clayton State Bursar Office
sp_instance.widget_parameters:
{ "html": { "value": "

How to Make Payments to the Clayton State Bursar Office

Step 1: Make the first payment to the Bursar Office in Edgewater Hall. Students must also turn in a copy of their completed Application Contract when making the first payment.

Step 2: Students may make the remaining payments for the study abroad program online, by following the instructions below; or continue to make the payments at the Bursar Office.

Step 3: Log onto the DUCK through the SWAN Click on the following via the DUCK:

  1. Student Services
  2. Student Accounts
  3. Account Summary by Term or Account Summary (either works)
  4. Scroll all the way to the bottom
  5. On the far right side choose “Credit Card Payment”
  6. Select Term
  7. Submit
  8. Enter credit card information
  9. Submit payment

Note: Make sure to select the correct term.

*If you have any difficulty with making your payments online, contact the Bursar Office at 678-466-4295 or visit the Bursar website to find more information.
